    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p>
                    <bibl><ptr target="#CIG"/><citedRange> 5157 b</citedRange> (part)</bibl>, from 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#pacho1827"/>, pl. <citedRange>LXVI.1</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SGDI"/> <citedRange>4864</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#oliverioTacc"/>, <citedRange>XII.87</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>199b</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>007400</citedRange></bibl>.
                Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#cassels1955"/>, p. <citedRange>34</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#dthorn-thorn2009"/>, p. <citedRange>223</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63024"><name nymRef="#Ἀράτα">Ἀράτας</name></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Sépulture</supplied> d'Arata.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Burial place of</supplied> Arata.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Sepoltura</supplied> di Arata.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>(مكان دفن) أراتا</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
             <p>Another Hellenistic mention (<ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr007300</ref>) and other mentions of Roman date (<ref type="inscription" target="https://ircyr2020.inslib.kcl.ac.uk/en/inscriptions/C.516.html">IRCyr2020 C.516</ref>)
                    were given in an assemblage in Pacho'drawing, thus edited by Franz  for the <bibl><ptr target="#CIG"/></bibl> as from one and the same tomb. 
                    Oliverio' transcriptions probably did not mention <bibl><ptr target="#CIG"/> <citedRange>5157</citedRange></bibl>
                    and Pugliese Carratelli at <bibl><ptr target="#SECir"/></bibl> thus ignored the identification. However, we gained from that republication a precise layout of the various inscriptions 
                    inside the tomb and measures of the letters. In between, <bibl><ptr target="#cassels1955"/></bibl> had mentioned for tomb S 74 'Inscriptions inside'.
                    His copy of the inscriptions were eventually made available by <bibl><ptr target="#dthorn-thorn2009"/></bibl>, allowing to connect inscriptions and tomb.</p>
	               <p>From Pacho's copy it was already possible to divide the inscriptions between the Hellenistic and Roman periods.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
    </text>
